@title An ERC token for Gold
@dev Returns the amount of tokens in existence.
@dev Returns the name of the token.
@dev Returns the symbol of the token.
@dev Returns the decimals places of the token.
@dev Returns the amount of tokens owned by `account`
@dev Returns the remaining number of tokens that `spender` will be allowed to spend on behalf of `owner` through {transferFrom}. This is zero by default.

Approval(address,address,uint256).details: Emitted when the allowance of a `spender` for an `owner` is set by a call to {approve}. `value` is the new allowance.

Transfer(address,address,uint256).details: Emitted when `value` tokens are moved from one account (`from`) to another (`to`).

approve(address,uint256).details: Sets `amount` as the allowance of `spender` over the caller's tokens. Emits an {Approval} event.

returns._0: Returns a boolean value indicating whether the operation succeeded.

transfer(address,uint256).details: Moves `amount` tokens from the caller's account to `recipient`. Emits a {Transfer} event.

returns._0: Returns a boolean value indicating whether the operation succeeded.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: Moves `amount` tokens from `sender` to `recipient` using the allowance mechanism. `amount` is then deducted from the caller's allowance. Emits a {Transfer} event.

returns._0: Returns a boolean value indicating whether the operation succeeded.

allowances.details: Returns the remaining number of tokens that `spender` will be allowed to spend on behalf of `owner` through {transferFrom}. This is zero by default.

balanceOf.details: Returns the amount of tokens owned by `account`

decimals.details: Returns the decimals places of the token.

name.details: Returns the name of the token.

symbol.details: Returns the symbol of the token.

totalSupply.details: Returns the amount of tokens in existence.

approve(address,uint256).notice: Allows _spender to withdraw from your account multiple times, up to the _value amount. If this function is called again it overwrites the current allowance with _value.

transfer(address,uint256).notice: Transfers amount of tokens to address, and MUST fire the Transfer event.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).notice: Transfers amount of tokens from address `_from` to address `_to`, and MUST fire the Transfer event.
